%N A072716 Integers expressible as (x^3 + y^3 + z^3)/(x*y*z) with positive integers x, y and z. (Alternatively, the integers expressible as x/y + y/z + z/x with positive integers x, y and z.)
%C A072716 It is easy to see that the numbers of the form m^2 + 5 are included in this sequence for m = 0, 1, 2, .... It is known that no number of any of the forms below appears in the sequence: (a) multiples of 4, (b) numbers congruent to 7 mod 8, (c) numbers of the form 2^m*k + 3 with odd numbers m >= 3 and k >= 1. It is also known, on the other hand, that there are infinitely many numbers congruent to 1, 2, 3, 5, or 6 mod 8 included in the sequence.
%C A072716 There are other parametric representations (like m^2 + 5) with positive a, b and c: (see example below for generating expressions): k = (m^2 + 33)/2: 17, 21, 29, 41, 57, 77, 101, 129, 161, 197, 237, 281, 329, 381, 437, 497, ...; k = m^4 + 8*m^2 + 4*m + 13: ..., 818, 381, 154, 53, 18, 13, 26, 69, 178, 413, 858, ...; k = m^4 - 2*m^3 + 4*m^2 + 3: ..., 978, 451, 174, 51, 10, 3, 6, 19, 66, 195, 478, ... - Erik Dofs (erik.dofs(AT)swipnet.se), Mar 06 2004
